args: The battles in the Milon Plains were harsh,\nbut in the end, New Alberia won the day.
Thus was peace visited on the region at long last.
I can't believe how much money goes into\nmy pocket without those imperial taxes!
Welcome! Perhaps some of our fine\nsylvan goods might catch your fancy?\nEvery piece is guaranteed handmade!
These people have barely had time to\nknow freedom, yet look how lively they\nalready are.
His Majesty's first action was to institute\nan across-the-board slashing of tariffs.
All of the merchants who had been unable\nto do business in this territory are now\nsurging into the area.
Patia! I'm from the village you saved!
Oh! The one that was surrounded?
Yes. I can't thank you enough for what you\ndid. I'm alive and my business is booming,\nand it's all thanks to you!
I am glad to hear it.
Did you hear? Patia's in town!
Wait, THE Patia? The Vice Captain\nof the White Sparrow Corps?!
Look, it's Patia! The noble knight who\ntook down a million imperials with a\nsingle sweep of her mighty spear!
I heard you swung your spear once and\nthe power of the wind you whipped up\nblew all the imperials away!
Show us! Show us how you cut through\nthose imperials that surrounded the village\nand tore 'em all to pieces!
I tore their FORMATION to pieces,\nnot the people themselves!
These people are turning my actions\ninto some kind of mad epoch!
That merely means you did excellent work.
I wanna be a strong knight\njust like you someday!
Don't look at me when I'm flustered!
I would have thought you were used to\nyoung girls singing your praises by now.
Well, I suppose they DO tend to\nhold me in a bit of esteem...
They'd say things like, ＂I want to marry\nyou when I grow up!＂ and such.
But this is the first time I've ever heard\nsomeone say they want to BECOME me.\nIt's all rather...embarrassing.
Heh. If it makes you feel any better,\nI know what you are going through.
In fact, the first time I heard someone say\nthey wanted to be like me, it was YOU.
Spare me the cheek! I remember.\nI simply never considered how it\nmight have embarrassed you.
When you said that to me, I chalked it\nup to a childish fantasy.
That's why I was surprised to see you\nat the White Sparrows entrance exam.
It seems you underestimated just\nhow much business I meant.
True enough. Yet at the same time,\nI felt an intense sense of responsibility.

I thought about your noble lineage,
despite having lost your court status.
And when I thought of how your parents
wanted to raise a proper, formal woman—

Enough! I know nothing of ladies or
lineage or the like. I simply wish to
be myself, no matter what blood
may run in my veins.
I threw those other things out long ago,\nCaptain Leif—back when I first met you.
Then it truly IS my responsibility.
The fort in the southwest of Rovetelle\nis under attack and requesting aid.
I see. Thank you, that will be all.
Shall I inform the Corps that we will be\nmoving out at once?
Please do, Patia. It seems we've more\nbattles yet ahead of us this day.
